        "created_at": "2025-06-30T08:19:45.122Z",
        "cooked": "<p>hi there,</p>\n<p>Since a couple of releases, Signal on My desktop PC (win10 Pro) flashes erratically black at odd times, even when generating the error debug log it flashed quite a bit, very odd. Just wanted to know if anybody else observed the same?</p>\n<p>Currently on RTX 4070 RTX, DCH 576.80</p>\n<p>This happens randomly, while scrolling through my personal messages, and after i have done a video call, or with linkedin open while having Signal open as well, etc.</p>\n<p>On my other PC a Zenbook with an Intel Iris XE, this doesn’t happen, same signal desktop, win10 Home.</p>\n<p>Recently changed something in our chromium browsers and currently using a different “angle” backend “d3d9” but i don’t think that is it “ANGLE graphics backend”</p>\n<p>I have the very same on the zenbook and works perfectly.</p>\n<p>Starting to happen a bit too often and flashing screen = bad for your <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/eyes.png?v=12\" title=\":eyes:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":eyes:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\">.</p>\n<p>thanks,<br>\nGabrio</p>",
